The skin is the largest organ of the human body and it needs to be treated with uttermost care. For most people, getting rid of dark spots on the hands and legs–particularly around the elbows and the knees–is a problem that presents a lot of difficulty. Check out these helpful tips below. Bottle pouring virgin olive oil in a bowl close up Olive oil contains healthy fatty acids and powerful antioxidants; therefore, olive oil is often used for skin care. Olive oil can soothe and moisturize your legs and your hands. If you want to have satisfactory results, repeat this treatment regularly. Photo Credit: Science Of Cooking Yoghurt contains large amounts of lactic acid. Lactic acid is beneficial in killing bacteria and germ causing skin itchiness and dryness. PHOTO CREDIT: google.com/search Avocado has a great source of vitamins, fatty acids, and antioxidants. Absorbed into the skin, they can help improve skin complexion. Avocados are also rich in Vitamin A which is beneficial in making the skin silky and smooth. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-464700 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-1062x598.jpg" alt="" width="1062" height="598" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/health-benefis-of-honey-1-e1519910748277-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/